          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1696330635402-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and a small splash of <strong>water </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes are starting to soften and the prawns are cooked</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1696330638424-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1696330638424-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1696330638424-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1696330638424-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1696330638424-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are soft, add your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> crème fraîche</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground sumac</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy harissa, charred pepper & king prawn gluten free spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: If it's looking a little dry add a splash more of the starchy pasta water</p>",
